1
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:06,756
[wind whooshing gently]

2
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:29,612
[eerie music playing]

3
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,165
[insects trilling]

4
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:45,711
[Samuel] <i>First, it came to Momma
as a snake...</i>

5
00:00:47,338 --> 00:00:48,339
[frog croaking]

6
00:00:48,422 --> 00:00:50,632
<i>then it took other forms
to torment her.</i>

7
00:00:53,469 --> 00:00:55,345
<i>But Momma was a good little girl,</i>

8
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:59,475
<i>she listened to her parents
and always stayed on the rope</i>

9
00:01:01,185 --> 00:01:03,187
<i>so The Evil couldn't touch her
outside the house.</i>

10
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:08,234
<i>Because if The Evil touches you,</i>

11
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:13,655
<i>it makes you do bad things.</i>

12
00:01:13,739 --> 00:01:14,948
[tense music sting]

13
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:27,503
- [screams]
- [gasps, pants]

14
00:01:32,341 --> 00:01:35,552
<i>[Momma] O blessed house of ancient wood.</i>

15
00:01:35,636 --> 00:01:39,264
Shelter to the pure and good.

16
00:01:39,348 --> 00:01:42,768
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

17
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:45,688
Heaven is here within our home.

18
00:01:46,522 --> 00:01:50,275
- [doorknob clacks]
- [door creaks]

19
00:01:50,359 --> 00:01:52,819
- [frog croaking]
- [insects trilling]

20
00:01:52,903 --> 00:01:53,904
[door creaks]

21
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,200
[owl hoots]

22
00:02:01,537 --> 00:02:03,247
- [animal whooshes]
- [door thuds]

23
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:06,125
[frog croaking]

24
00:02:11,797 --> 00:02:12,839
[floorboard creaking]

25
00:02:16,302 --> 00:02:18,595
- [frog croaking]
- [owl hooting]

26
00:02:48,292 --> 00:02:50,502
[croaking continues]

27
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:55,132
[croaking intensifies]

28
00:02:58,344 --> 00:03:00,804
- [grunting in distance]
- [gasps]

29
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:03,224
[shuddering breaths]

30
00:03:03,307 --> 00:03:06,768
[growling]

31
00:03:06,852 --> 00:03:09,020
[groaning, growling]

32
00:03:14,568 --> 00:03:17,195
- [growling]
- [gasps]

33
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:24,077
[growling stops]

34
00:03:26,163 --> 00:03:27,205
[door thuds]

35
00:03:28,290 --> 00:03:30,417
- [Momma sighs deeply]
- [door creaks]

36
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:34,588
[clanking]

37
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,472
[exhales]

38
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:45,432
[footsteps thudding]

39
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,568
[door creaking]

40
00:04:01,907 --> 00:04:04,117
[snoring]

41
00:04:04,201 --> 00:04:08,038
- [Koda breathing rapidly]
- [snoring continues]

42
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:31,228
Samuel, Nolan.

43
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,730
Ten-minute warning, boys.

44
00:04:32,813 --> 00:04:33,814
[Koda whines]

45
00:04:35,816 --> 00:04:38,443
[footsteps receding]

46
00:04:45,117 --> 00:04:46,743
Nine-minute warning, Nolan.

47
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:53,333
- [bed creaking]
- [bell jingling]

48
00:04:53,417 --> 00:04:55,752
[Samuel] <i>Momma says
there's only love inside of us.</i>

49
00:04:56,837 --> 00:04:58,964
<i>That's why The Evil wants us so badly.</i>

50
00:05:01,842 --> 00:05:03,552
<i>He wants to destroy this love,</i>

51
00:05:04,386 --> 00:05:07,055
<i>- make us turn against each other...</i>
- <i>[Koda</i> whines]

52
00:05:07,139 --> 00:05:08,265
<i>kill each other...</i>

53
00:05:11,769 --> 00:05:13,729
<i>like he made the people in the world do.</i>

54
00:05:15,272 --> 00:05:17,899
[footsteps receding]

55
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,948
[bell jingling]

56
00:05:24,031 --> 00:05:27,117
[Samuel] <i>All it needs is one touch
without the rope on.</i>

57
00:05:28,035 --> 00:05:30,871
<i>And then, not even the house can save you.</i>

58
00:05:31,705 --> 00:05:34,708
[ominous music playing]

59
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:16,834
[fire crackling]

60
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:54,663
[utensils and plates clinking]

61
00:06:59,251 --> 00:07:01,461
[footsteps tapping]

62
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:09,427
[Koda whines]

63
00:07:13,223 --> 00:07:15,391
[Nolan sighing]

64
00:07:27,112 --> 00:07:28,279
[Momma] Eat it. Get it.

65
00:07:30,157 --> 00:07:31,366
There you go.

66
00:07:32,368 --> 00:07:34,119
Frogs sang loud last night.

67
00:07:35,704 --> 00:07:38,248
- Spring is coming.
- We'll be ready.

68
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:40,208
It's a good day for a good day.

69
00:07:44,129 --> 00:07:45,380
[Koda grunts]

70
00:07:45,464 --> 00:07:46,923
Don't feed the dog.

71
00:07:47,007 --> 00:07:48,883
We're not the only ones starving.

72
00:07:53,263 --> 00:07:55,556
- And I don't need to eat as much as you.
- [Momma sighs]

73
00:08:00,604 --> 00:08:01,604
Momma?

74
00:08:02,731 --> 00:08:04,274
Momma, can we listen to it tonight'?

75
00:08:05,192 --> 00:08:07,152
- It's not a new moon.
- I'm asking Momma.

76
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:10,239
We should wait.
It won't be special if we don't.

77
00:08:10,322 --> 00:08:11,698
Told ya.

78
00:08:14,034 --> 00:08:15,952
[Nolan grunting softly]

79
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:21,958
[sighs deeply]

80
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,588
You'll grow into <i>'em.</i>

81
00:08:27,423 --> 00:08:29,341
[door creaking]

82
00:08:57,369 --> 00:08:59,537
[all] The Evil can't touch me here.

83
00:08:59,621 --> 00:09:01,664
Dawn to night and year to year.

84
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:04,293
The forest where this thing is bound,

85
00:09:04,376 --> 00:09:07,003
wrapped up tight and safe and sound.

86
00:09:15,804 --> 00:09:18,973
- [wind whooshing gently]
- [leaves rustling]

87
00:09:28,108 --> 00:09:29,109
[Koda whines]

88
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,365
[Koda panting]

89
00:09:35,449 --> 00:09:37,284
[eerie music sting]

90
00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:44,875
Do you see it?

91
00:09:59,223 --> 00:10:00,390
Go get him, Koda.

92
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:01,850
Bring us a big, fat rabbit.

93
00:10:05,854 --> 00:10:06,980
[Momma] Y'all ready?

94
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:13,195
Never let go.

95
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:15,864
Never let go.

96
00:10:17,616 --> 00:10:20,619
[dark music playing]

97
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:23,723
[Samuel] <i>Momma told us that even before
The Evil possessed everyone,</i>

98
00:11:23,807 --> 00:11:25,350
<i>the world was already bad.</i>

99
00:11:25,434 --> 00:11:27,060
[creaking]

100
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:28,186
<i>And that's Why it came.</i>

101
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:31,106
<i>The people opened their door for it,
whether they knew it or not.</i>

102
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:35,444
[indistinct voices]

103
00:11:35,527 --> 00:11:36,945
<i>[voice] Let them go...</i>

104
00:11:40,324 --> 00:11:41,484
<i>[Samuel] But Grandma knew it,</i>

105
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:44,369
<i>and Grandpa was the only one
to believe her.</i>

106
00:11:49,499 --> 00:11:51,751
<i>He was a good man
and built this place for her,</i>

107
00:11:52,836 --> 00:11:55,672
a <i>blessed house where The Evil
wouldn't be able to come in,</i>

108
00:11:57,090 --> 00:12:00,510
<i>a place to raise a family far away
from the darkness of the world.</i>

109
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:06,141
<i>It was a good life.</i>

110
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:09,937
<i>But after a while, Grandma started to feel
a presence lurking in the woods,</i>

111
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:14,524
<i>something evil getting stronger.</i>

112
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:16,526
<i>She refused to leave the house anymore.</i>

113
00:12:17,277 --> 00:12:21,197
<i>So Grandpa figured out how to tie the rope
to the foundation of the house</i>

114
00:12:21,281 --> 00:12:23,074
<i>so she could finally go outside.</i>

115
00:12:24,576 --> 00:12:26,828
[ominous music plays]

116
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:30,415
[exhales, grunts]

117
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:34,252
[ominous breathing]

118
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:38,757
[wind whooshing]

119
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,467
<i>[voice] Let them go, Junebug.</i>

120
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:46,640
[bird caws]

121
00:12:46,723 --> 00:12:48,474
[squeaking]

122
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:02,989
[thudding]

123
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:05,783
[grunts]

124
00:13:09,913 --> 00:13:11,497
Whoo!

125
00:13:11,581 --> 00:13:13,082
Whoo-hoo!

126
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:16,795
[whimsical music playing]

127
00:13:23,635 --> 00:13:27,138
[panting, grunting]

128
00:13:45,532 --> 00:13:47,909
[frog croaking]

129
00:14:00,630 --> 00:14:05,130
[crunching]

130
00:14:06,970 --> 00:14:08,054
[grunting]

131
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:17,939
[grunting]

132
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:48,761
[grunts]

133
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:55,518
[effort grunting]

134
00:15:00,732 --> 00:15:01,732
[grunts]

135
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:11,117
Nolan.

136
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:13,662
What are you doing?

137
00:15:13,745 --> 00:15:16,205
Making some slack so I can grab this egg.

138
00:15:16,289 --> 00:15:17,623
Don't.

139
00:15:18,875 --> 00:15:20,251
Could be a trick.

140
00:15:20,335 --> 00:15:22,420
I could grab it. It's right there.

141
00:15:22,504 --> 00:15:24,130
Give me your machete.

142
00:15:24,214 --> 00:15:25,214
No.

143
00:15:27,050 --> 00:15:28,468
We'll let Momma decide.

144
00:15:28,552 --> 00:15:30,303
She can tie the ropes together.

145
00:15:32,848 --> 00:15:33,848
[blows]

146
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:40,772
[leaves rustle]

147
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:45,985
I wasn't gonna let go.

148
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:49,864
We didn't get this far
just to die of hunger.

149
00:15:49,948 --> 00:15:51,866
How can you be so sure of everything?

150
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:53,390
[Samuel] Because I'm older than you.

151
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:55,745
[Nolan] Yeah, by three minutes.

152
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:04,087
[Samuel] She loves me more.

153
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,589
What?

154
00:16:05,672 --> 00:16:07,215
[ominous music plays]

155
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:09,759
- What?
- What did you say?

156
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:13,680
I didn't say anything.

157
00:16:13,763 --> 00:16:15,556
[ominous music buildup]

158
00:16:25,358 --> 00:16:27,526
[yells, grunts]

159
00:16:28,528 --> 00:16:29,654
Sam!

160
00:16:31,114 --> 00:16:32,990
- [cracks]
- [yells]

161
00:16:33,074 --> 00:16:34,492
Sam! [whistle blowing]

162
00:16:37,537 --> 00:16:38,537
[gasps]

163
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:40,540
Sam!

164
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:42,667
- [whistle blowing]
- [grunting]

165
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:46,713
Nolan!

166
00:16:46,796 --> 00:16:48,255
Samuel!

167
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:51,092
[groaning]

168
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:52,886
[whistle blowing]

169
00:16:52,969 --> 00:16:53,970
[Nolan] Sam!

170
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:56,222
[whistle blowing]

171
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:58,641
My rope.

172
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:00,977
- [gasps]
- [groans]

173
00:17:01,853 --> 00:17:03,437
[cracking, rustling]

174
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:07,733
- [Samuel grunting]
- [rattling]

175
00:17:10,153 --> 00:17:11,154
[Nolan] Samuel!

176
00:17:11,238 --> 00:17:14,366
[rattling intensifies]

177
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:17,827
Sam!

178
00:17:18,745 --> 00:17:22,039
Sam! [grunting]

179
00:17:22,123 --> 00:17:23,707
Samuel!

180
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:25,794
- [whimpering]
- Sam!

181
00:17:25,877 --> 00:17:28,254
[panting]

182
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,301
Nolan!

183
00:17:34,135 --> 00:17:35,052
No!

184
00:17:35,136 --> 00:17:37,471
- Get back on the rope!
- [Nolan grunting]

185
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:39,266
[grunting]

186
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:42,560
[effort grunting, panting]

187
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:46,815
[growls, hisses]

188
00:17:46,898 --> 00:17:48,649
[Samuel groaning]

189
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:52,570
[growling]

190
00:17:52,654 --> 00:17:56,449
- [knife clinks]
- [growling]

191
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:59,702
- [grunting]
- [growling, hissing]

192
00:17:59,786 --> 00:18:01,329
No!

193
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:04,332
No! No! No! No!

194
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:07,961
[grunting]

195
00:18:08,044 --> 00:18:10,671
[hissing]

196
00:18:10,755 --> 00:18:13,632
[grunting]

197
00:18:13,717 --> 00:18:16,553
[panting]

198
00:18:18,221 --> 00:18:21,515
- [panting]
- [groaning]

199
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,643
Did it touch you? Huh?

200
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:25,103
- [panting]
- [groaning]

201
00:18:25,186 --> 00:18:26,395
Did it touch you, Nolan?

202
00:18:26,479 --> 00:18:27,897
I don't... I don't think so.

203
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:29,649
[growling]

204
00:18:34,362 --> 00:18:35,988
[Momma] Hold on to the rope.

205
00:18:36,072 --> 00:18:37,364
[hissing]

206
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:41,995
[Nolan] What do you see?
Momma, what is it?

207
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,293
- [grunting]
- Breathe. Just breathe.

208
00:18:49,377 --> 00:18:52,671
[breathing shakily]

209
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:55,425
[gurgling, hissing]

210
00:18:55,508 --> 00:18:58,969
- [Samuel grunting]
- [Momma] Breathe. Breathe.

211
00:18:59,054 --> 00:19:01,347
It's okay. It's okay. Just breathe.

212
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:02,432
Just breathe.

213
00:19:02,515 --> 00:19:04,183
[shuddering, breathing heavily]

214
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:07,562
[Samuel grunting]

215
00:19:11,107 --> 00:19:13,526
[Momma] On your knees. I need to be sure.

216
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:14,610
[clinks]

217
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:18,281
Don't look at me. Touch the wood!

218
00:19:18,365 --> 00:19:20,033
Hands on the cellar.

219
00:19:20,116 --> 00:19:21,367
Say it.

220
00:19:28,291 --> 00:19:29,375
Say it!

221
00:19:30,418 --> 00:19:33,879
[both] O blessed house of ancient wood.

222
00:19:33,963 --> 00:19:36,507
Shelter to the pure and good.

223
00:19:36,591 --> 00:19:39,885
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

224
00:19:39,969 --> 00:19:42,972
Heaven is here within our home.

225
00:19:50,605 --> 00:19:51,606
Okay, get up.

226
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:55,401
- [Samuel groaning]
- [grunting]

227
00:19:55,485 --> 00:19:57,525
- [Momma] What happened?
- [Nolan] I didn't mean to.

228
00:19:57,821 --> 00:20:00,782
- I stepped on his rope...
- Have you lost your mind?

229
00:20:00,865 --> 00:20:03,242
- It's all right, Momma. He didn't...
- Quiet!

230
00:20:03,326 --> 00:20:05,036
One more second

231
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:08,248
and it would've all been over
for all of us!

232
00:20:08,331 --> 00:20:10,875
That rope is your lifeline.

233
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:12,895
- [Nolan] I'm sorry.
- I don't need you to be sorry!

234
00:20:12,919 --> 00:20:14,921
I need you to use your head!

235
00:20:15,004 --> 00:20:17,297
[groaning, panting]

236
00:20:18,591 --> 00:20:20,509
- [shoe thuds]
- [exhales sharply]

237
00:20:27,225 --> 00:20:28,601
Oh...

238
00:20:28,685 --> 00:20:30,269
Can you move it?

239
00:20:30,353 --> 00:20:31,771
[Samuel groans]

240
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:33,106
I think it's broke.

241
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:41,322
[jars clinking]

242
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,159
Don't just stand there.

243
00:20:45,243 --> 00:20:46,827
Get me a splint for his ankle.

244
00:20:48,663 --> 00:20:50,539
[footsteps receding]

245
00:20:50,623 --> 00:20:52,333
[groaning]

246
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:54,585
- I know, <i>I</i> know.
- [whimpering]

247
00:20:54,669 --> 00:20:56,420
Come on. Come on.

248
00:20:56,504 --> 00:20:57,796
- It's okay.
- [groaning]

249
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,387
What'd it look like this time?

250
00:21:10,685 --> 00:21:11,686
Like my Momma.

251
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:16,816
It's trying to scare me...

252
00:21:18,943 --> 00:21:21,362
<i>like it tried to scare my Momma before.</i>

253
00:21:30,371 --> 00:21:31,914
[chair creaking]

254
00:21:31,998 --> 00:21:34,208
[ominous music playing]

255
00:21:49,182 --> 00:21:51,184
[rustling]

256
00:21:53,102 --> 00:21:54,603
[hissing]

257
00:22:16,334 --> 00:22:17,960
[Momma] That's all we got today.

258
00:22:20,213 --> 00:22:21,589
Don't eat too fast.

259
00:22:24,008 --> 00:22:25,092
Sure is good.

260
00:22:33,142 --> 00:22:34,184
[sighs]

261
00:22:42,402 --> 00:22:44,112
[Momma] I used to be thankful

262
00:22:44,946 --> 00:22:47,823
that The Evil didn't show itself to you.

263
00:22:51,244 --> 00:22:54,664
And then, I figured out what it was doing.

264
00:22:58,710 --> 00:23:00,336
I never told y'all this.

265
00:23:01,337 --> 00:23:02,379
But one time,

266
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:05,257
it came to me as a little girl,

267
00:23:06,467 --> 00:23:07,926
crying out for help.

268
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:13,224
She was just at my rope's limit.

269
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:18,438
She got her foot stuck in a gopher hole.

270
00:23:20,899 --> 00:23:23,484
She was howling, screaming.

271
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:24,652
[screaming]

272
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,071
I saw the bone

273
00:23:28,364 --> 00:23:29,406
sticking out.

274
00:23:31,242 --> 00:23:33,869
I had to keep telling myself
that it wasn't real.

275
00:23:33,953 --> 00:23:37,206
But the screams went on for days.

276
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:41,919
So every morning, I went out to check...

277
00:23:44,005 --> 00:23:45,715
to see if The Evil had given up.

278
00:23:48,593 --> 00:23:50,011
But she was still there.

279
00:23:51,054 --> 00:23:54,140
Her skin turned blue and gray.

280
00:23:55,224 --> 00:23:56,725
[flies buzzing]

281
00:23:57,477 --> 00:23:58,478
The smell...

282
00:23:58,561 --> 00:24:01,146
[ominous music sting]

283
00:24:01,230 --> 00:24:03,273
I wondered why she was still out there.

284
00:24:04,484 --> 00:24:05,484
Why?

285
00:24:06,402 --> 00:24:09,113
Because it wanted me
to go see about that girl.

286
00:24:10,448 --> 00:24:12,450
It wanted me to doubt myself.

287
00:24:13,576 --> 00:24:15,703
To lure me off the rope.

288
00:24:16,579 --> 00:24:18,163
The Evil is clever

289
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:21,292
and patient.

290
00:24:22,377 --> 00:24:25,588
It's like the snake
you've seen in the woods.

291
00:24:25,672 --> 00:24:29,384
Evil can wear many, many skins.

292
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:34,597
And the greatest trick of all

293
00:24:34,681 --> 00:24:36,599
is playing on you, boys.

294
00:24:37,433 --> 00:24:39,852
And when enough time goes by,

295
00:24:39,936 --> 00:24:41,938
you're gonna forget it's even there.

296
00:24:42,814 --> 00:24:45,066
You're gonna let your guard down.

297
00:24:46,067 --> 00:24:48,152
- And it's gonna get you!
- [gasps]

298
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:52,364
One touch

299
00:24:53,866 --> 00:24:55,450
without a rope on

300
00:24:57,078 --> 00:25:00,998
is all it takes to possess one of us

301
00:25:01,082 --> 00:25:02,958
and get inside the house.

302
00:25:03,793 --> 00:25:04,794
Never...

303
00:25:06,170 --> 00:25:07,296
let go.

304
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:11,217
- Never let go.
- Never let go.

305
00:25:14,345 --> 00:25:16,347
[floorboard creaking]

306
00:25:18,391 --> 00:25:20,684
[breathing shakily]

307
00:25:29,902 --> 00:25:31,612
[door creaks, opens]

308
00:25:36,743 --> 00:25:37,744
How long?

309
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:39,912
About an hour.

310
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:42,248
Felt longer tonight.

311
00:25:42,331 --> 00:25:44,124
Did you imagine it?

312
00:25:48,838 --> 00:25:49,838
Yes.

313
00:25:52,508 --> 00:25:53,675
Tell us about it.

314
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:56,470
I imagined it was all gone.

315
00:25:57,889 --> 00:25:58,889
You...

316
00:26:00,308 --> 00:26:01,600
Sam...

317
00:26:02,852 --> 00:26:03,978
Koda.

318
00:26:05,396 --> 00:26:06,397
The house.

319
00:26:09,025 --> 00:26:11,193
All I had left was the darkness.

320
00:26:11,944 --> 00:26:13,153
And then what?

321
00:26:14,655 --> 00:26:16,698
I thought about our birth in the house

322
00:26:16,783 --> 00:26:18,993
and how safe it keeps us every day.

323
00:26:19,994 --> 00:26:22,287
And I felt the darkness float away.

324
00:26:23,164 --> 00:26:24,331
Look around.

325
00:26:26,042 --> 00:26:27,418
Look how lucky you are.

326
00:26:28,127 --> 00:26:30,129
All your dreams came true.

327
00:26:31,047 --> 00:26:32,882
The Evil can't touch you here.

328
00:26:34,509 --> 00:26:36,928
Samuel, your turn.

329
00:26:37,011 --> 00:26:38,429
Time to clean your soul.

330
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:48,230
Remember, lose us completely
and then find us again.

331
00:26:48,314 --> 00:26:51,066
Fill the cellar up with all your love.

332
00:26:51,150 --> 00:26:54,486
You remind the house
Why we deserve its protection.

333
00:26:59,283 --> 00:27:00,367
[door closes]

334
00:27:00,451 --> 00:27:04,371
- [thunder rumbling
- [rain pattering]

335
00:27:06,165 --> 00:27:07,791
[Samuel] Can I move yet?

336
00:27:07,875 --> 00:27:09,293
[Nolan] Nope.

337
00:27:09,377 --> 00:27:11,128
Nolan, I got an itch.

338
00:27:11,212 --> 00:27:12,630
I said, "Don't move."

339
00:27:13,464 --> 00:27:14,756
It's just one itch.

340
00:27:17,051 --> 00:27:18,051
Okay.

341
00:27:20,012 --> 00:27:21,054
That should do it.

342
00:27:26,060 --> 00:27:29,104
Wow. Are those owl wings?

343
00:27:29,188 --> 00:27:30,188
Uh-huh.

344
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:33,275
I can fly anywhere I want.

345
00:27:33,359 --> 00:27:34,818
And eat whatever you want.

346
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:37,863
Once upon a time,

347
00:27:37,947 --> 00:27:42,447
there was a boy who could fly
and catch all the squirrels in the trees.

348
00:27:45,580 --> 00:27:47,748
[hooting]

349
00:27:50,751 --> 00:27:52,586
[both chuckling]

350
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:02,221
Hey, Sam.

351
00:28:03,514 --> 00:28:07,017
After your rope broke,
did you notice anything?

352
00:28:08,644 --> 00:28:09,770
Like what?

353
00:28:09,854 --> 00:28:11,105
Anything strange.

354
00:28:11,189 --> 00:28:13,524
That was the first time we ever let go.

355
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:17,111
And nothing changed.

356
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,821
'Cause it didn't get us.

357
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:21,323
Yeah.

358
00:28:28,247 --> 00:28:29,373
If it did...

359
00:28:30,291 --> 00:28:32,751
do you think Momma woulda killed us?

360
00:28:34,795 --> 00:28:36,087
Like she killed Poppa?

361
00:28:39,217 --> 00:28:40,927
Like she killed Grandma and Grandpa?

362
00:28:41,552 --> 00:28:42,928
The Evil touched them.

363
00:28:44,138 --> 00:28:45,931
She was protecting us.

364
00:28:46,015 --> 00:28:47,182
I know that.

365
00:28:47,266 --> 00:28:48,267
[book thuds]

366
00:28:52,188 --> 00:28:53,731
[thunder rumbling]

367
00:28:53,814 --> 00:28:55,023
What?

368
00:28:55,107 --> 00:28:56,107
Nothing.

369
00:29:01,113 --> 00:29:02,989
You ever wish you could run free
like Koda?

370
00:29:04,033 --> 00:29:05,409
Without a rope around your chest?

371
00:29:05,493 --> 00:29:07,119
But Koda's a dog.

372
00:29:07,203 --> 00:29:09,413
The Evil doesn't care about animals.

373
00:29:13,751 --> 00:29:15,294
[thunder crashing]

374
00:29:17,421 --> 00:29:19,840
[thunder rumbling]

375
00:29:26,931 --> 00:29:29,600
You ever wish you could see what she sees?

376
00:29:29,684 --> 00:29:30,726
Just once?

377
00:29:33,771 --> 00:29:36,565
I felt something getting closer today.

378
00:29:37,358 --> 00:29:38,609
You were just scared.

379
00:29:41,612 --> 00:29:43,447
Why are you asking all these questions?

380
00:29:44,615 --> 00:29:46,491
Momma never lied to us.

381
00:29:52,957 --> 00:29:56,502
[thunder rumbling]

382
00:29:56,585 --> 00:29:58,211
"She loves me more."

383
00:30:00,881 --> 00:30:03,800
That's what I heard you say
before I stepped on your rope.

384
00:30:03,884 --> 00:30:04,968
I didn't say that.

385
00:30:10,683 --> 00:30:12,601
I didn't mean for what happened.

386
00:30:14,687 --> 00:30:15,938
I know.

387
00:30:16,022 --> 00:30:18,524
[thunder rumbling]

388
00:30:22,570 --> 00:30:25,447
[blade clinking]

389
00:30:30,328 --> 00:30:32,955
[chair creaking]

390
00:31:04,945 --> 00:31:06,863
[rustling]

391
00:31:06,947 --> 00:31:08,406
[man] O blessed house...

392
00:31:11,869 --> 00:31:13,203
of ancient wood.

393
00:31:14,830 --> 00:31:15,830
Home...

394
00:31:17,041 --> 00:31:18,584
to my runaway wife.

395
00:31:27,843 --> 00:31:29,344
Hey, Junebug.

396
00:31:33,516 --> 00:31:34,558
What's wrong?

397
00:31:37,353 --> 00:31:38,353
June!

398
00:31:39,730 --> 00:31:40,730
June!

399
00:31:43,692 --> 00:31:44,776
June, it's me.

400
00:31:50,533 --> 00:31:51,617
It's been a while.

401
00:31:53,744 --> 00:31:55,162
God, have I missed you.

402
00:31:57,164 --> 00:31:58,456
You think I can see 'em?

403
00:32:03,754 --> 00:32:06,256
Oh, you ain't told 'em the truth
about their father.

404
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:08,842
I get it.

405
00:32:10,302 --> 00:32:12,595
'Cause then you got to tell 'em
who you really are.

406
00:32:13,889 --> 00:32:15,932
Ain't that right, my little Junebug?

407
00:32:16,016 --> 00:32:17,559
I'm not her no more.

408
00:32:18,352 --> 00:32:19,644
You know you loved it.

409
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:23,816
- What's your plan?
- [door creaks]

410
00:32:23,899 --> 00:32:24,900
I know ya.

411
00:32:25,609 --> 00:32:26,818
You ain't got no plan.

412
00:32:27,945 --> 00:32:29,863
You might as well give 'em to me.

413
00:32:29,947 --> 00:32:31,949
Or would you rather watch them starve?

414
00:32:38,372 --> 00:32:40,082
I came so close today.

415
00:32:46,755 --> 00:32:47,797
Sooner or later...

416
00:32:49,133 --> 00:32:50,342
you're gonna let go.

417
00:32:51,677 --> 00:32:52,969
And when you do...

418
00:32:58,225 --> 00:33:00,727
I'm gonna... [distorted]
make you eat your babies.

419
00:33:02,563 --> 00:33:03,563
June!

420
00:33:04,398 --> 00:33:05,816
- [distorted] June!
- [door slams]

421
00:33:13,449 --> 00:33:15,576
Careful now. Don't break those roots.

422
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,958
You think it'll get better?

423
00:33:23,042 --> 00:33:24,334
Hard to say.

424
00:33:25,127 --> 00:33:27,254
The winter did a number on us.

425
00:33:27,338 --> 00:33:29,757
All we can do now is hope.

426
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:33,427
What?

427
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:34,595
Nothing.

428
00:33:40,809 --> 00:33:42,185
The snake on your back...

429
00:33:43,354 --> 00:33:45,481
You said you got it
when you were in the city.

430
00:33:46,690 --> 00:33:50,443
But you also said The Evil
was already there, killing everybody.

431
00:33:51,695 --> 00:33:54,489
- I don't understand...
- I got it before it all started.

432
00:33:55,908 --> 00:33:57,242
When I met your Poppa.

433
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:00,496
I was a different person back then.

434
00:34:01,413 --> 00:34:02,455
Does it still scare you?

435
00:34:03,707 --> 00:34:06,459
Not anymore. I like it now.

436
00:34:08,087 --> 00:34:09,087
Why?

437
00:34:09,713 --> 00:34:11,548
Because it's from your life before.

438
00:34:12,716 --> 00:34:13,758
In the old world.

439
00:34:14,677 --> 00:34:17,012
A world full of pain and suffering?

440
00:34:18,013 --> 00:34:19,389
What's to like about that?

441
00:34:22,893 --> 00:34:23,893
Huh?

442
00:34:24,645 --> 00:34:25,646
Don't know.

443
00:34:26,355 --> 00:34:27,773
When I was your age,

444
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:31,151
asking questions like you do...

445
00:34:32,528 --> 00:34:34,363
I didn't really believe my Momma, either.

446
00:34:35,364 --> 00:34:37,240
- That's why you left?
- Mm-hmm.

447
00:34:37,908 --> 00:34:39,701
Never thought I'd come back here.

448
00:34:41,245 --> 00:34:44,248
But it's the only place
I could keep y'all safe.

449
00:34:44,331 --> 00:34:48,084
But what if The Evil did, touch one of us
and come in the house?

450
00:34:49,003 --> 00:34:50,212
What would happen?

451
00:34:52,047 --> 00:34:53,840
It would make us kill each other.

452
00:34:54,675 --> 00:34:56,093
That's how the world ended.

453
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:04,643
But how do you know we're alone?

454
00:35:04,727 --> 00:35:07,521
Maybe our house isn't the only one
that's protected.

455
00:35:07,605 --> 00:35:09,773
Would that make you feel better?

456
00:35:09,857 --> 00:35:11,775
We wouldn't be alone
for the rest of our lives.

457
00:35:11,859 --> 00:35:14,862
We're not alone, Nolan.
We have each other.

458
00:35:15,946 --> 00:35:17,238
And that's everything.

459
00:35:19,158 --> 00:35:21,368
There's nobody else out there, baby.

460
00:35:23,537 --> 00:35:24,746
We're the world now.

461
00:35:25,748 --> 00:35:29,543
[uneasy music playing]

462
00:35:41,847 --> 00:35:43,348
[Momma] <i>"Once upon a time,</i>

463
00:35:43,432 --> 00:35:46,685
there dwelt near a large wood
a poor woodcutter,

464
00:35:46,769 --> 00:35:49,021
<i>with his wife and two children...</i>

465
00:35:51,023 --> 00:35:53,567
<i>a little boy called Hansel</i>

466
00:35:53,651 --> 00:35:55,444
<i>and a girl called Gretel.</i>

467
00:35:55,527 --> 00:35:58,821
<i>Once, when there was a great famine
in the land,</i>

468
00:35:58,906 --> 00:36:01,366
<i>he could not procure
even his daily bread."</i>

469
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:02,576
[grunts]

470
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:05,829
"As they lay there thinking
in the bed one evening,

471
00:36:05,913 --> 00:36:07,581
rolling about for trouble...

472
00:36:09,416 --> 00:36:11,209
<i>he sighed and said to his wife,</i>

473
00:36:12,378 --> 00:36:14,588
<i>'What will become of us?</i>

474
00:36:15,881 --> 00:36:18,133
How will I feed my children

475
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:22,804
<i>when we have no more
that we can eat ourselves?'</i>

476
00:36:23,931 --> 00:36:26,767
<i>'Know, then, my husband, ' answered she,</i>

477
00:36:26,850 --> 00:36:28,643
<i>'we will lead them away,</i>

478
00:36:29,937 --> 00:36:32,022
<i>quite early in the morning</i>

479
00:36:32,106 --> 00:36:34,858
<i>into the thickest part of the woods.</i>

480
00:36:35,693 --> 00:36:37,903
<i>And there make them a fire</i>

481
00:36:37,986 --> 00:36:40,738
and give them each
a little piece of bread.'

482
00:36:40,823 --> 00:36:43,283
[effort grunting, yelling]

483
00:36:44,201 --> 00:36:48,371
<i>'And then we will go to our work
and leave them alone.</i>

484
00:36:48,455 --> 00:36:50,957
<i>They will not find a way home again.</i>

485
00:36:52,334 --> 00:36:55,045
<i>And we shall be freed from them.</i>

486
00:37:11,729 --> 00:37:13,856
- [Nolan] It's new.
- [Samuel] You sure?

487
00:37:13,939 --> 00:37:15,565
You got eyes, don't you?

488
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:18,735
It's a new moon. Right, Momma?

489
00:37:19,903 --> 00:37:21,321
Can we listen to it tonight?

490
00:37:22,948 --> 00:37:25,951
[whirring]

491
00:37:29,621 --> 00:37:34,121
["The Big Rock Candy Mountain"
by Van Hunt playing]

492
00:37:48,474 --> 00:37:49,641
[Koda whines]

493
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:53,020
[Nolan chuckles]

494
00:37:53,103 --> 00:37:54,312
Come on, Momma.

495
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:24,801
[song continues playing]

496
00:38:42,903 --> 00:38:45,030
[song muffles, fades]

497
00:38:49,076 --> 00:38:51,912
[unsettling music playing]

498
00:39:07,135 --> 00:39:08,761
[breathing heavily]

499
00:39:29,533 --> 00:39:31,243
- [exhales]
- [floorboard creaks]

500
00:39:33,161 --> 00:39:36,706
[ominous music playing]

501
00:39:36,790 --> 00:39:37,790
Nolan?

502
00:39:38,792 --> 00:39:40,001
Nolan.

503
00:39:40,085 --> 00:39:41,836
[water splashes]

504
00:39:49,261 --> 00:39:50,553
Are you still asleep?

505
00:39:52,389 --> 00:39:53,306
Nolan.

506
00:39:53,390 --> 00:39:54,599
There you go.

507
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:58,603
[grunts] You forgot your bell again.

508
00:39:58,687 --> 00:40:01,773
[bell jingling]

509
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:05,277
- [rain pattering]
- [thunder rumbling]

510
00:40:07,863 --> 00:40:08,863
[grunts gently]

511
00:40:33,555 --> 00:40:35,765
[stream flowing]

512
00:40:48,236 --> 00:40:50,238
[wind whooshing gently]

513
00:41:19,810 --> 00:41:20,810
[sighs]

514
00:41:21,603 --> 00:41:22,604
[grunts]

515
00:41:27,401 --> 00:41:29,277
[raven cawing]

516
00:41:34,324 --> 00:41:35,324
[raven cawing]

517
00:41:46,128 --> 00:41:47,170
[cawing]

518
00:41:51,091 --> 00:41:52,717
[cawing, munching]

519
00:41:55,971 --> 00:41:57,013
[gasps]

520
00:42:09,568 --> 00:42:10,568
[raven caws]

521
00:42:17,868 --> 00:42:19,995
[cawing]

522
00:42:23,331 --> 00:42:24,332
- [cracks]
- [caws]

523
00:42:28,170 --> 00:42:30,255
[breathing heavily]

524
00:42:30,338 --> 00:42:32,256
[screams]

525
00:42:32,340 --> 00:42:34,842
- [thudding]
- [breathing heavily]

526
00:42:43,226 --> 00:42:44,143
[grunts]

527
00:42:44,227 --> 00:42:46,854
[uneasy music playing]

528
00:43:29,397 --> 00:43:30,689
It's better with sap.

529
00:43:33,068 --> 00:43:36,696
Yeah. That'll make it
taste less like a tree.

530
00:43:44,246 --> 00:43:45,914
<i>[Momma] We're doing the best we can.</i>

531
00:43:47,374 --> 00:43:48,374
Eat.

532
00:44:09,437 --> 00:44:11,063
[rustling]

533
00:44:16,319 --> 00:44:17,320
[blade clinks, thuds]

534
00:44:18,363 --> 00:44:19,572
[bell jingles]

535
00:44:26,913 --> 00:44:28,331
Momma?

536
00:44:28,415 --> 00:44:29,415
Sam?

537
00:44:30,333 --> 00:44:32,126
[bell jingles]

538
00:44:35,714 --> 00:44:37,590
[rustling]

539
00:44:38,884 --> 00:44:42,596
[grunts, screams]

540
00:44:42,679 --> 00:44:44,097
No!

541
00:44:44,181 --> 00:44:46,224
No! [grunting]

542
00:44:46,308 --> 00:44:48,435
No! [grunting]

543
00:44:48,518 --> 00:44:49,810
No! No!

544
00:44:53,440 --> 00:44:55,275
- [insects trilling]
- [gasping]

545
00:44:55,358 --> 00:44:57,026
[bell jingles]

546
00:45:00,739 --> 00:45:02,991
[breathing shakily]

547
00:45:06,036 --> 00:45:07,996
- [animal growls]
- [frog croaks]

548
00:45:08,079 --> 00:45:09,330
[rustling]

549
00:45:10,957 --> 00:45:14,335
[breathing heavily]

550
00:45:24,095 --> 00:45:25,095
Koda.

551
00:45:29,309 --> 00:45:31,060
[door thuds]

552
00:45:32,854 --> 00:45:34,730
[floorboard thudding]

553
00:45:34,814 --> 00:45:36,148
[Momma] Touch the wood.

554
00:45:36,233 --> 00:45:37,400
Say it!

555
00:45:37,484 --> 00:45:39,527
O blessed house of ancient wood.

556
00:45:39,611 --> 00:45:42,280
Shelter to the pure and good.

557
00:45:42,364 --> 00:45:44,908
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

558
00:45:44,991 --> 00:45:47,118
Heaven is here within our home.

559
00:45:47,202 --> 00:45:48,244
[Momma] Say it again.

560
00:45:48,328 --> 00:45:50,371
O blessed house of ancient wood...

561
00:45:50,455 --> 00:45:51,581
Again!

562
00:45:51,665 --> 00:45:53,917
- O blessed house of ancient wood.
- Louder!

563
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,002
Shelter to the pure and good!

564
00:45:57,170 --> 00:45:59,172
[bell jingling]

565
00:45:59,256 --> 00:46:01,174
[Nolan whimpers] Momma...

566
00:46:07,430 --> 00:46:08,431
Momma!

567
00:46:11,434 --> 00:46:12,893
I have to pee, Momma!

568
00:46:14,145 --> 00:46:15,396
Momma!

569
00:46:31,579 --> 00:46:33,789
Did you feel the darkness go away?

570
00:46:35,750 --> 00:46:38,002
[creaking]

571
00:46:38,086 --> 00:46:39,670
[owl hooting]

572
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:46,803
[uneasy music playing]

573
00:46:57,647 --> 00:46:58,647
Sam...

574
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:01,359
You awake?

575
00:47:02,944 --> 00:47:04,278
[Samuel] No.

576
00:47:04,362 --> 00:47:05,404
Sam.

577
00:47:06,906 --> 00:47:08,073
Sam!

578
00:47:09,159 --> 00:47:10,160
Yes?

579
00:47:11,619 --> 00:47:13,078
We need to leave the house.

580
00:47:13,163 --> 00:47:14,747
Goodnight, Nolan.

581
00:47:15,707 --> 00:47:16,833
I'm serious.

582
00:47:17,584 --> 00:47:18,918
- Sam!
- [shushes]

583
00:47:24,674 --> 00:47:26,050
How do you wanna leave?

584
00:47:27,177 --> 00:47:30,013
The Evil will catch us
as soon as we take off the rope.

585
00:47:30,096 --> 00:47:31,097
We know the forest.

586
00:47:31,181 --> 00:47:34,267
If we look after each other,
we might have a chance to outrun it.

587
00:47:34,976 --> 00:47:36,519
What about Momma?

588
00:47:36,603 --> 00:47:38,980
We'll come back for her
once we find something to eat.

589
00:47:40,231 --> 00:47:41,899
Momma knows what's right for us.

590
00:47:41,983 --> 00:47:43,901
I don't think she does anymore.

591
00:47:45,070 --> 00:47:46,446
Did you see her?

592
00:47:46,529 --> 00:47:47,947
She's starving too.

593
00:47:49,574 --> 00:47:51,254
[Samuel] She always figures something out.

594
00:47:52,327 --> 00:47:53,953
[Nolan] For once, we have to help her.

595
00:47:55,580 --> 00:47:56,914
[Samuel] By disobeying her?

596
00:47:57,832 --> 00:47:59,667
Will you really let go of the rope?

597
00:48:06,966 --> 00:48:08,300
I can let go of the rope,

598
00:48:09,636 --> 00:48:11,387
but I can't let go of my brother.

599
00:48:23,900 --> 00:48:25,234
It's too dangerous.

600
00:48:27,278 --> 00:48:28,279
I'm sorry.

601
00:48:32,826 --> 00:48:36,120
[distant crunching sound]

602
00:48:38,915 --> 00:48:41,042
- [hisses]
- [tense music sting]

603
00:48:43,586 --> 00:48:45,713
[Koda barks, pants]

604
00:49:01,563 --> 00:49:03,314
[soft music plays]

605
00:49:03,398 --> 00:49:06,359
[grunting]

606
00:49:19,414 --> 00:49:20,414
[sniffles]

607
00:49:22,000 --> 00:49:23,000
[exhales sharply]

608
00:49:52,822 --> 00:49:55,032
This is a very special tool.

609
00:49:56,618 --> 00:49:57,785
It's called a camera.

610
00:50:01,080 --> 00:50:02,706
What does it do'?

611
00:50:02,790 --> 00:50:04,041
Takes pictures.

612
00:50:06,836 --> 00:50:09,213
It captures what it sees

613
00:50:09,297 --> 00:50:10,715
with this little eye.

614
00:50:13,301 --> 00:50:14,385
You aim it,

615
00:50:15,303 --> 00:50:18,222
then you push
this button right here, and...

616
00:50:18,306 --> 00:50:19,640
[whooshing]

617
00:50:20,475 --> 00:50:22,518
A real-life picture comes out.

618
00:50:28,399 --> 00:50:29,608
Like this one.

619
00:50:30,610 --> 00:50:31,819
This was me...

620
00:50:33,196 --> 00:50:34,530
from the old world.

621
00:50:36,366 --> 00:50:37,784
Is that really you?

622
00:50:37,867 --> 00:50:39,577
- [grunts]
- Hey, hey, careful.

623
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:45,708
I was a different person back then.

624
00:50:53,132 --> 00:50:54,258
Or this one.

625
00:50:59,639 --> 00:51:01,515
I took it outside on the porch.

626
00:51:03,518 --> 00:51:04,518
Sam.

627
00:51:08,982 --> 00:51:11,150
- This is us?
- Mm-hmm.

628
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:12,735
And this is Koda.

629
00:51:12,819 --> 00:51:14,779
- [whines]
- [Momma] Yep.

630
00:51:16,030 --> 00:51:18,323
You can take a picture
of anything you want.

631
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:22,829
But a good picture shows more
than what the camera's looking at.

632
00:51:24,664 --> 00:51:28,751
It shows a special moment, frozen in time.

633
00:51:28,835 --> 00:51:30,628
They can even show a feeling.

634
00:51:31,879 --> 00:51:33,380
Like love.

635
00:51:39,929 --> 00:51:40,930
Where's Poppa?

636
00:51:42,682 --> 00:51:44,600
He was holding the camera.

637
00:51:44,684 --> 00:51:46,477
Do you have a picture of him?

638
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:48,270
Mm-mm.

639
00:51:49,147 --> 00:51:51,232
These are the only two I chose to keep.

640
00:51:53,818 --> 00:51:57,071
And there's one more in there too.
I've been saving it.

641
00:51:57,739 --> 00:51:58,865
For when?

642
00:52:01,534 --> 00:52:02,910
Look for the right moment.

643
00:52:03,661 --> 00:52:07,915
Maybe you'll find one that reminds us
What we're living for.

644
00:52:07,999 --> 00:52:09,875
Even if it's something small.

645
00:52:11,127 --> 00:52:13,170
'Cause some moments in life are hard.

646
00:52:14,714 --> 00:52:18,217
But when we remember why we're holding on,

647
00:52:18,968 --> 00:52:20,427
we get strong again.

648
00:52:29,062 --> 00:52:30,354
This right here

649
00:52:31,606 --> 00:52:34,025
is about to be one of those hard moments.

650
00:52:40,406 --> 00:52:44,535
We've been through some brutal,
brutal winters, haven't we?

651
00:52:44,619 --> 00:52:46,078
But nothing like this one.

652
00:52:46,871 --> 00:52:48,914
Everything in the garden, gone.

653
00:52:50,667 --> 00:52:52,502
The roots are waterlogged.

654
00:52:55,213 --> 00:52:57,215
The animals, they ain't come back yet.

655
00:52:58,591 --> 00:52:59,675
We got water.

656
00:53:00,510 --> 00:53:02,178
But that'll last us, maybe...

657
00:53:03,012 --> 00:53:04,346
a couple weeks.

658
00:53:04,430 --> 00:53:05,556
Maybe a month.

659
00:53:10,186 --> 00:53:11,312
<i>But soon...</i>

660
00:53:15,024 --> 00:53:16,191
our bodies...

661
00:53:17,318 --> 00:53:18,902
are gonna start shutting down.

662
00:53:23,408 --> 00:53:24,659
And we're gonna die.

663
00:53:34,043 --> 00:53:35,878
So we only got one option.

664
00:53:40,425 --> 00:53:41,551
And that's Koda.

665
00:53:42,593 --> 00:53:43,635
What?

666
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:45,054
We can salt the meat.

667
00:53:45,138 --> 00:53:48,224
Maybe it'll last us a month or so
and before it's spoiled...

668
00:53:48,307 --> 00:53:49,307
No!

669
00:53:51,728 --> 00:53:53,938
I know you love him. We all do.

670
00:53:54,021 --> 00:53:56,898
But he nearing the end of his life,
and he...

671
00:53:56,983 --> 00:53:59,819
- he ain't caught us nothing in months.
- We can eat more frogs.

672
00:53:59,902 --> 00:54:01,612
That's not gonna be enough.

673
00:54:01,696 --> 00:54:03,924
I'll eat the bark, the bugs.
I don't mind it, Momma. I swear.

674
00:54:03,948 --> 00:54:05,259
- Nolan.
- Maybe it's safe to leave.

675
00:54:05,283 --> 00:54:06,826
I was out there without a rope on.

676
00:54:06,909 --> 00:54:08,512
The Evil coulda touched me, but it didn't.

677
00:54:08,536 --> 00:54:11,163
'Cause it chose not to.
It wants you to doubt me.

678
00:54:11,247 --> 00:54:12,289
And look...

679
00:54:13,291 --> 00:54:15,561
- that's exactly what you're doing.
- What if you're wrong?

680
00:54:15,585 --> 00:54:17,065
What if the world is still out there?

681
00:54:17,128 --> 00:54:18,671
This is the world!

682
00:54:18,755 --> 00:54:20,465
There's nothing out there!
[slams table]

683
00:54:20,548 --> 00:54:22,800
It's either the house or The Evil.
That's it!

684
00:54:22,884 --> 00:54:24,677
No. This is evil.

685
00:54:24,761 --> 00:54:26,596
Eating family is evil!

686
00:54:26,679 --> 00:54:29,723
If we can't feed ourselves,
how are we gonna feed the dog?

687
00:54:29,807 --> 00:54:31,809
- You wanna die?
- I don't wanna die,

688
00:54:31,893 --> 00:54:33,936
but I don't wanna see my friend die!

689
00:54:34,020 --> 00:54:35,730
But this is not fair!

690
00:54:35,813 --> 00:54:38,023
All he's done is protect us!

691
00:54:40,902 --> 00:54:42,028
Let's ask Samuel.

692
00:54:43,529 --> 00:54:45,155
Of course he'll do what you say.

693
00:54:45,239 --> 00:54:47,157
He can talk for hisself.

694
00:54:49,452 --> 00:54:50,453
Samuel?

695
00:54:56,417 --> 00:54:57,626
We have to.

696
00:54:57,710 --> 00:54:59,044
I hate you!

697
00:54:59,128 --> 00:55:01,088
I hate both of you! I hate this house!

698
00:55:01,172 --> 00:55:02,298
I hate this house!

699
00:55:03,549 --> 00:55:04,550
Come on, Koda.

700
00:55:10,014 --> 00:55:11,014
[door slams]

701
00:55:12,683 --> 00:55:15,310
Momma, I can do it if you want.

702
00:55:19,482 --> 00:55:20,774
No.

703
00:55:20,858 --> 00:55:23,443
[door opens, creaks]

704
00:55:23,528 --> 00:55:27,323
[footsteps approaching]

705
00:55:27,406 --> 00:55:28,406
[Koda whines]

706
00:55:33,830 --> 00:55:34,830
[Nolan] No.

707
00:55:37,124 --> 00:55:38,583
- No!
- [Koda whimpers]

708
00:55:38,668 --> 00:55:40,294
No. No!

709
00:55:40,378 --> 00:55:43,047
No! No! No!

710
00:55:44,090 --> 00:55:45,674
Koda! Koda!

711
00:55:45,758 --> 00:55:47,593
No!

712
00:55:47,677 --> 00:55:49,845
No! Momma, please!

713
00:55:49,929 --> 00:55:51,388
Please, no!

714
00:55:51,472 --> 00:55:52,681
Koda!

715
00:55:54,684 --> 00:55:55,685
Koda!

716
00:55:56,435 --> 00:55:57,477
Please!

717
00:55:59,063 --> 00:56:00,063
[cries]

718
00:56:14,245 --> 00:56:15,579
You're a good dog.

719
00:56:16,455 --> 00:56:19,666
[voice breaking] I thank you
for taking good care of us.

720
00:56:19,750 --> 00:56:21,835
[Koda whimpers]

721
00:56:25,339 --> 00:56:26,965
[sobbing]

722
00:56:34,098 --> 00:56:37,601
[kisses, sobs] You're a good dog.

723
00:56:40,771 --> 00:56:43,064
[crossbow clacks]

724
00:56:45,902 --> 00:56:47,111
[breathes deeply]

725
00:56:59,874 --> 00:57:03,627
[Koda whimpers, pants]

726
00:57:12,136 --> 00:57:13,762
- [Koda whimpers]
- [groans]

727
00:57:16,766 --> 00:57:18,851
[sobs, exhales deeply]

728
00:57:21,062 --> 00:57:23,147
[Koda whimpers]

729
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:28,360
Momma.

730
00:57:29,737 --> 00:57:30,737
[gasps]

731
00:57:31,739 --> 00:57:33,824
- Nolan.
- It's not real.

732
00:57:36,452 --> 00:57:37,453
Listen to me.

733
00:57:41,123 --> 00:57:42,457
You need to see.

734
00:57:42,541 --> 00:57:45,293
You need to see
there's nothing to be scared of!

735
00:57:45,378 --> 00:57:47,338
That's what it wants you to think, baby.

736
00:57:47,421 --> 00:57:49,881
Don't do it! No! Don't do it. No!

737
00:57:51,342 --> 00:57:54,511
- Nolan! Open this door. Nolan!
- [bangs door]

738
00:57:56,097 --> 00:57:57,473
Open the door.

739
00:57:57,556 --> 00:58:00,058
- Nolan!
- [bangs door]

740
00:58:01,477 --> 00:58:04,354
Nolan, I-I lied.

741
00:58:04,438 --> 00:58:07,566
I didn't tell you everything.
I brought The Evil here.

742
00:58:07,650 --> 00:58:09,318
The Evil is real!

743
00:58:09,402 --> 00:58:12,071
And if it touches me
and gets inside the house,

744
00:58:12,154 --> 00:58:13,864
it's gonna make me kill you!

745
00:58:13,948 --> 00:58:15,366
Open the door.

746
00:58:16,325 --> 00:58:17,326
Please!

747
00:58:18,119 --> 00:58:19,954
[screams] Open the fucking door!

748
00:58:21,288 --> 00:58:22,998
[grunting]

749
00:58:24,291 --> 00:58:25,208
Nolan!

750
00:58:25,292 --> 00:58:27,043
- [Samuel roars]
- [grunts]

751
00:58:30,297 --> 00:58:33,466
[both grunting]

752
00:58:35,511 --> 00:58:37,554
[grunting]

753
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:41,392
- [Grandma] Bad little goat.
- [Momma panting]

754
00:58:42,435 --> 00:58:45,771
- [gasps]
- Bad little goat.

755
00:58:45,855 --> 00:58:49,859
Bad little goat...
[distorted] caught sitting in my chair.

756
00:58:51,694 --> 00:58:56,031
Let's see that tushy, and I'll make it
so you can't sit anywhere.

757
00:58:56,115 --> 00:58:57,282
It's here!

758
00:58:57,366 --> 00:58:59,034
- [grunting]
- It's here!

759
00:58:59,869 --> 00:59:02,997
- Momma!
- [grunting]

760
00:59:05,249 --> 00:59:06,458
[shakily] It's here.

761
00:59:06,542 --> 00:59:08,210
[bleating] Bad!

762
00:59:08,294 --> 00:59:11,839
Bad!

763
00:59:11,922 --> 00:59:16,422
Bad little goat,
putting poison in my food.

764
00:59:16,844 --> 00:59:19,930
Bad little goat.

765
00:59:20,014 --> 00:59:21,724
[distorted bleating] Bad!

766
00:59:22,975 --> 00:59:27,475
I told you, I'm gonna make you
eat your baby.

767
00:59:29,899 --> 00:59:31,650
You'll never get in.

768
00:59:33,694 --> 00:59:35,153
No!

769
00:59:36,030 --> 00:59:39,324
[squelching, gurgling]

770
00:59:39,408 --> 00:59:40,492
[glass thuds]

771
00:59:42,369 --> 00:59:44,746
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

772
00:59:49,376 --> 00:59:51,378
- [grunts]
- [groans]

773
00:59:53,756 --> 00:59:54,756
Momma!

774
00:59:59,970 --> 01:00:00,970
Momma?

775
01:00:01,972 --> 01:00:03,890
Wake up, Momma.

776
01:00:03,974 --> 01:00:05,225
Momma, wake up!

777
01:00:11,899 --> 01:00:13,984
It's okay, Momma.
I'm tying the ropes together.

778
01:00:16,862 --> 01:00:18,697
It's okay, Momma. It's okay.

779
01:00:18,781 --> 01:00:19,907
Momma, please.

780
01:00:24,537 --> 01:00:26,539
O blessed house of ancient wood.

781
01:00:26,622 --> 01:00:29,541
Shelter to the pure and good.

782
01:00:29,625 --> 01:00:32,252
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

783
01:00:33,295 --> 01:00:35,422
Heaven is here within our home.

784
01:00:38,259 --> 01:00:39,802
Momma, please.

785
01:00:40,678 --> 01:00:42,596
The house has us now, Momma.

786
01:00:42,680 --> 01:00:45,516
You can wake up. Please, Momma, wake up.

787
01:00:46,517 --> 01:00:47,726
I need you.

788
01:00:47,810 --> 01:00:49,228
Please, Momma.

789
01:00:49,311 --> 01:00:51,271
[sobbing, sniffling]

790
01:00:53,399 --> 01:00:55,901
O blessed house of ancient wood.

791
01:00:55,985 --> 01:00:58,612
Shelter to the pure and good.

792
01:00:58,696 --> 01:01:01,448
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

793
01:01:01,532 --> 01:01:03,575
Heaven is here within our home.

794
01:01:04,827 --> 01:01:06,370
Momma, please.

795
01:01:09,331 --> 01:01:10,415
Please, Momma.

796
01:01:12,710 --> 01:01:14,712
[Samuel sobbing]

797
01:01:42,239 --> 01:01:44,282
["Our Love" by Starr Sisters playing]

798
01:01:44,283 --> 01:01:44,364
["Our Love" by Starr Sisters playing]

799
01:01:44,365 --> 01:01:45,845
["Our Love" by Starr Sisters playing]

800
01:02:26,492 --> 01:02:29,453
- [thudding]
- [song fading]

801
01:02:32,498 --> 01:02:36,460
[wind whooshing gently]

802
01:02:40,506 --> 01:02:41,798
Koda!

803
01:02:46,178 --> 01:02:47,762
Koda!

804
01:02:47,846 --> 01:02:52,308
[panting]

805
01:02:52,393 --> 01:02:53,435
[Nolan] Koda!

806
01:02:54,478 --> 01:02:56,646
Koda! Come back!

807
01:02:56,730 --> 01:02:58,106
[whimpers]

808
01:02:58,190 --> 01:02:59,399
Koda!

809
01:03:10,828 --> 01:03:12,830
[blowing]

810
01:03:42,985 --> 01:03:45,862
[door creaks]

811
01:03:45,946 --> 01:03:47,447
I made some pine needle tea.

812
01:03:48,407 --> 01:03:49,825
It'll help with your hunger.

813
01:03:52,786 --> 01:03:54,287
Was that you out there?

814
01:03:57,541 --> 01:03:58,542
Out where?

815
01:04:01,170 --> 01:04:02,337
I saw you

816
01:04:03,505 --> 01:04:04,839
in the woods

817
01:04:05,883 --> 01:04:08,802
laughing at me
for not being able to save her.

818
01:04:08,886 --> 01:04:10,345
[coughs]

819
01:04:12,181 --> 01:04:13,515
I think you were dreaming.

820
01:04:17,728 --> 01:04:18,937
Touch the wood.

821
01:04:22,775 --> 01:04:23,817
Touch it.

822
01:04:30,866 --> 01:04:34,077
[both] O blessed house of ancient wood.

823
01:04:34,161 --> 01:04:36,955
Shelter to the pure and good.

824
01:04:37,039 --> 01:04:40,333
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

825
01:04:40,417 --> 01:04:42,961
Heaven is here within our home.

826
01:04:51,303 --> 01:04:53,722
Okay. Now drink.

827
01:04:57,142 --> 01:04:58,393
We need some air.

828
01:05:01,522 --> 01:05:04,441
[groaning]

829
01:05:06,693 --> 01:05:07,985
I won't let you die.

830
01:05:26,839 --> 01:05:29,842
[uneasy music playing]

831
01:05:39,101 --> 01:05:40,727
[rustling]

832
01:06:10,924 --> 01:06:12,717
[insects trilling]

833
01:06:41,038 --> 01:06:42,122
[grunts]

834
01:06:53,175 --> 01:06:56,094
[wind whooshing gently]

835
01:07:01,850 --> 01:07:03,268
Help!

836
01:07:04,603 --> 01:07:06,104
Help!

837
01:07:08,815 --> 01:07:10,024
Hello!

838
01:07:14,196 --> 01:07:17,032
[grunting]

839
01:07:22,329 --> 01:07:23,872
Help!

840
01:07:40,597 --> 01:07:41,681
Excuse me!

841
01:07:43,308 --> 01:07:44,350
Hi there.

842
01:07:45,435 --> 01:07:47,437
Sorry to intrude. I just, uh...

843
01:07:48,146 --> 01:07:50,231
I was hiking and I...

844
01:07:50,315 --> 01:07:52,191
I thought I heard someone
screaming for help.

845
01:07:52,276 --> 01:07:54,528
That wasn't you, by any chance, was it?

846
01:07:56,113 --> 01:07:59,616
I... I thought my ears
were playing tricks on me.

847
01:07:59,700 --> 01:08:00,992
[chuckles]

848
01:08:02,619 --> 01:08:04,495
Wow, I didn't think anyone was out here.

849
01:08:04,580 --> 01:08:05,622
This is, uh...

850
01:08:07,874 --> 01:08:08,874
Huh.

851
01:08:15,299 --> 01:08:16,300
Are you okay?

852
01:08:21,054 --> 01:08:22,221
What's your name, son?

853
01:08:24,266 --> 01:08:25,266
[whispers] Nolan.

854
01:08:28,186 --> 01:08:29,562
I'm sorry, I didn't catch that.

855
01:08:30,314 --> 01:08:31,857
- Nolan.
- Nolan.

856
01:08:33,150 --> 01:08:34,526
Hi, Nolan. I'm Cole.

857
01:08:35,986 --> 01:08:37,195
It's nice to meet you.

858
01:08:38,322 --> 01:08:39,322
So...

859
01:08:41,199 --> 01:08:43,492
where your folks at? They around?

860
01:08:45,495 --> 01:08:46,871
My Momma's dead.

861
01:08:46,955 --> 01:08:48,957
Oh, I'm very sorry to hear that.

862
01:08:51,501 --> 01:08:52,919
How did she pass?

863
01:08:54,171 --> 01:08:55,547
My brother's sick.

864
01:08:55,631 --> 01:08:57,007
He needs food.

865
01:08:57,090 --> 01:08:59,759
Okay. Well, I've got some food in my pack.

866
01:09:01,845 --> 01:09:03,346
You know...

867
01:09:03,430 --> 01:09:06,141
Nolan, I've got a truck
about five miles from here,

868
01:09:06,224 --> 01:09:08,453
- and I could take you and your brother...
- [Samuel] Get back!

869
01:09:08,477 --> 01:09:10,520
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Okay. Okay, okay.

870
01:09:10,604 --> 01:09:13,189
Whoa. Okay.

871
01:09:13,273 --> 01:09:17,068
Uh... look,
I don't mean you boys any harm.

872
01:09:17,152 --> 01:09:19,070
Nolan here says you're sick.

873
01:09:19,988 --> 01:09:21,739
- We're not stupid.
- Sam.

874
01:09:21,823 --> 01:09:24,033
I didn't say you were stupid. I just...

875
01:09:24,951 --> 01:09:27,328
I just thought someone was in trouble.

876
01:09:27,412 --> 01:09:28,996
- That's it.
- You killed my Momma.

877
01:09:29,081 --> 01:09:30,332
No, son. I...

878
01:09:30,415 --> 01:09:32,583
I don't know your Momma. Okay?

879
01:09:32,668 --> 01:09:34,586
Look, this was just... This was a mistake.

880
01:09:34,670 --> 01:09:35,837
<i>I'm sorry. I'm gonna go.</i>

881
01:09:35,921 --> 01:09:37,482
- I'm gonna leave now, all right'? I ju...
- Don't move.

882
01:09:37,506 --> 01:09:40,258
I just... Okay. Just calm down.

883
01:09:40,342 --> 01:09:42,218
What if he's a real person?

884
01:09:42,302 --> 01:09:43,386
We were happy.

885
01:09:45,972 --> 01:09:47,264
Listen to me, okay?

886
01:09:48,100 --> 01:09:50,435
I'm just gonna turn,
I'm just gonna go back,

887
01:09:50,519 --> 01:09:52,604
I'm gonna go back
from Where I came from, all right?

888
01:09:52,688 --> 01:09:54,898
- Just...
- I said, "Don't move!"

889
01:09:54,981 --> 01:09:56,482
[exhales sharply]

890
01:09:57,609 --> 01:09:58,901
Look, everything's fine.

891
01:09:59,903 --> 01:10:01,743
- [Nolan] Just let him go.
- Everything's okay.

892
01:10:02,364 --> 01:10:03,573
Let him go, Sam.

893
01:10:06,410 --> 01:10:07,410
Please.

894
01:10:08,453 --> 01:10:09,454
It's over.

895
01:10:10,706 --> 01:10:11,832
She's gone.

896
01:10:15,836 --> 01:10:17,003
- No!
- [Samuel grunts]

897
01:10:19,339 --> 01:10:20,757
[groaning]

898
01:10:20,841 --> 01:10:21,758
Sam...

899
01:10:21,842 --> 01:10:23,134
[Cole groaning]

900
01:10:29,224 --> 01:10:31,017
[groaning]

901
01:10:31,101 --> 01:10:32,894
Help me!

902
01:10:32,978 --> 01:10:34,437
[yells in pain]

903
01:10:34,521 --> 01:10:36,022
Help me!

904
01:10:38,233 --> 01:10:39,400
Help!

905
01:10:39,484 --> 01:10:41,736
- Nolan, don't.
- He said he has food.

906
01:10:41,820 --> 01:10:44,280
- It's a trick.
- Help me!

907
01:10:44,364 --> 01:10:46,366
[Nolan panting]

908
01:11:15,145 --> 01:11:17,021
[Cole coughs, grunts]

909
01:11:21,735 --> 01:11:26,030
[gurgling, groaning]

910
01:11:33,413 --> 01:11:34,413
[gasps]

911
01:11:37,292 --> 01:11:40,003
- [line ringing]
- [gasping for breath]

912
01:11:42,088 --> 01:11:44,465
- [groans]
- [line rings]

913
01:11:44,549 --> 01:11:46,149
[dispatcher] <i>911. What's your emergency?</i>

914
01:11:48,178 --> 01:11:49,596
[gurgling]

915
01:11:49,679 --> 01:11:52,431
<i>Sir? Sir, can you hear me?</i>

916
01:11:53,975 --> 01:11:56,102
- Can you <i>tell me...</i>
- [gasps]

917
01:11:56,186 --> 01:11:58,938
[both grunting]

918
01:11:59,022 --> 01:12:01,774
[dispatcher] <i>Sir,
can you tell me Where you are?</i>

919
01:12:01,858 --> 01:12:06,358
[grunting]

920
01:12:06,613 --> 01:12:08,906
[panting]

921
01:12:08,990 --> 01:12:10,950
[dispatcher] <i>Sir, tell me Where you are.</i>

922
01:12:11,034 --> 01:12:12,160
[grunts]

923
01:12:19,751 --> 01:12:20,751
[knife clinks]

924
01:12:31,221 --> 01:12:32,931
[gasps, effort grunts]

925
01:12:37,519 --> 01:12:39,729
[effort grunts]

926
01:12:41,857 --> 01:12:43,859
[sniffs, chuckles]

927
01:12:50,991 --> 01:12:54,202
Mmm. [breathes heavily]

928
01:12:56,913 --> 01:13:00,082
[door creaks]

929
01:13:00,166 --> 01:13:02,960
- [door closes]
- Mmm. [breathes heavily]

930
01:13:07,507 --> 01:13:08,591
It's from the man.

931
01:13:10,927 --> 01:13:11,969
He's dead.

932
01:13:15,015 --> 01:13:16,224
That wasn't a man.

933
01:13:18,310 --> 01:13:19,311
Try it.

934
01:13:20,270 --> 01:13:21,312
Did you let go?

935
01:13:22,314 --> 01:13:23,314
No.

936
01:13:24,274 --> 01:13:25,900
I touched him with the rope on.

937
01:13:25,984 --> 01:13:28,361
He wouldn't have let me
if he was The Evil, right?

938
01:13:29,529 --> 01:13:31,405
You still won't learn.

939
01:13:31,489 --> 01:13:34,283
You're falling for it all over again!

940
01:13:34,367 --> 01:13:36,035
Just try it.

941
01:13:40,457 --> 01:13:41,457
No.

942
01:13:42,042 --> 01:13:43,752
Maybe there's no evil.

943
01:13:44,669 --> 01:13:46,128
Momma lied to us.

944
01:13:47,839 --> 01:13:49,966
We're not the only ones left in the world.

945
01:13:50,842 --> 01:13:52,653
If we thought
there was nothing out there for us,

946
01:13:52,677 --> 01:13:53,997
then we wouldn't wanna leave her.

947
01:13:54,054 --> 01:13:57,223
She killed herself to keep us safe
and you still won't believe it!

948
01:13:57,307 --> 01:13:59,517
- Just try it!
- [thuds]

949
01:14:00,727 --> 01:14:02,353
You'll see that it's real!

950
01:14:03,438 --> 01:14:05,523
It'll make you feel better!

951
01:14:08,652 --> 01:14:09,861
I promise.

952
01:14:12,572 --> 01:14:16,033
Once upon a time, there were two brothers
who trusted each other.

953
01:14:16,117 --> 01:14:17,535
She loved you!

954
01:14:18,995 --> 01:14:20,287
She loved you.

955
01:14:21,998 --> 01:14:23,916
And I'm so sorry for what I did.

956
01:14:28,713 --> 01:14:30,005
But we're not safe.

957
01:14:33,218 --> 01:14:34,594
We're dying.

958
01:14:35,637 --> 01:14:37,639
At least then we'll be with Momma again.

959
01:14:38,974 --> 01:14:41,142
Maybe that'll be enough for you this time.

960
01:14:47,816 --> 01:14:50,819
- [ominous music playing]
- [insects trilling]

961
01:14:56,866 --> 01:14:58,868
[wind whooshing]

962
01:15:32,944 --> 01:15:34,487
[snoring]

963
01:16:21,326 --> 01:16:24,537
- [chair creaking]
- [clicking]

964
01:16:39,886 --> 01:16:41,429
- [thuds]
- [gasps]

965
01:17:03,868 --> 01:17:04,868
Hello?

966
01:17:08,498 --> 01:17:09,707
Who's in there?

967
01:17:11,042 --> 01:17:12,042
Koda?

968
01:17:18,091 --> 01:17:19,091
Hello?

969
01:17:19,717 --> 01:17:20,926
[tense music sting]

970
01:17:25,723 --> 01:17:27,933
[unsettling music playing]

971
01:17:34,816 --> 01:17:36,484
- [tense music sting]
- [yells]

972
01:17:37,485 --> 01:17:38,485
Momma?

973
01:17:48,121 --> 01:17:51,207
[flies buzzing]

974
01:17:53,710 --> 01:17:55,211
- [girl] Hello?
- [gasps]

975
01:17:59,007 --> 01:18:00,758
I'm looking for my dad.

976
01:18:02,552 --> 01:18:05,930
He asked me to wait by the car,
but he never came back.

977
01:18:09,350 --> 01:18:11,185
Do you mind lowering that?

978
01:18:16,274 --> 01:18:17,274
Thanks.

979
01:18:18,943 --> 01:18:20,194
How did you get here?

980
01:18:22,238 --> 01:18:23,989
I followed his footsteps in the mud.

981
01:18:25,950 --> 01:18:29,286
He's tall, black hair,
a bit of gray on the sides?

982
01:18:30,997 --> 01:18:32,081
Have you seen him?

983
01:18:39,923 --> 01:18:42,008
Why is that rope around your waist?

984
01:18:44,761 --> 01:18:45,928
To keep me safe.

985
01:18:47,222 --> 01:18:48,223
From what?

986
01:18:54,604 --> 01:18:56,355
Where did you get that flashlight?

987
01:18:59,817 --> 01:19:01,068
That's my dad's.

988
01:19:02,320 --> 01:19:03,738
It was a mistake.

989
01:19:05,240 --> 01:19:06,824
I didn't mean to.

990
01:19:06,908 --> 01:19:08,117
What are you talking about?

991
01:19:08,826 --> 01:19:09,868
Where is he?

992
01:19:14,666 --> 01:19:15,792
What did you do?

993
01:19:15,875 --> 01:19:17,459
What did you do to him?

994
01:19:19,003 --> 01:19:20,504
I thought he was The Evil.

995
01:19:21,923 --> 01:19:23,424
No, wait!

996
01:19:27,262 --> 01:19:29,013
I thought he was The Evil!

997
01:19:30,640 --> 01:19:32,141
Come back!

998
01:19:32,225 --> 01:19:35,228
[suspenseful music playing]

999
01:19:39,607 --> 01:19:40,691
[grunting]

1000
01:19:47,240 --> 01:19:48,449
Come back! [grunts]

1001
01:19:54,205 --> 01:19:56,040
The rope... Oh, no.

1002
01:20:03,756 --> 01:20:05,841
Please! Come back! [effort grunting]

1003
01:20:14,767 --> 01:20:16,101
I know she's real.

1004
01:20:23,443 --> 01:20:24,735
- [thudding]
- [gasps]

1005
01:20:30,450 --> 01:20:31,868
[grunting]

1006
01:20:37,790 --> 01:20:40,417
- [rustling]
- [voices laughing]

1007
01:20:40,501 --> 01:20:42,294
[panting]

1008
01:20:47,717 --> 01:20:48,801
- [rustling]
- [gasps]

1009
01:20:50,845 --> 01:20:52,680
[insects trilling]

1010
01:21:01,314 --> 01:21:03,899
- [thudding]
- [gasping]

1011
01:21:15,870 --> 01:21:17,121
[scuttling]

1012
01:21:18,706 --> 01:21:20,916
[rattling]

1013
01:22:02,458 --> 01:22:04,668
[growls]

1014
01:22:04,752 --> 01:22:05,961
[yells]

1015
01:22:06,045 --> 01:22:08,672
- [gurgling]
- [yelling]

1016
01:22:11,092 --> 01:22:15,096
[gasping breaths]

1017
01:22:21,978 --> 01:22:25,648
[distorted, gasping breaths]

1018
01:22:31,446 --> 01:22:32,363
[exhales deeply]

1019
01:22:32,447 --> 01:22:35,199
[clinking]

1020
01:22:36,993 --> 01:22:39,412
[door opens, creaks]

1021
01:22:41,414 --> 01:22:43,541
[door closes, thuds]

1022
01:22:47,670 --> 01:22:48,879
Sam!

1023
01:23:00,850 --> 01:23:02,017
Sam!

1024
01:23:27,668 --> 01:23:29,086
Sam!

1025
01:23:37,512 --> 01:23:39,138
[Samuel] Nolan!

1026
01:23:40,473 --> 01:23:41,473
Sam?

1027
01:23:42,725 --> 01:23:43,725
Sam!

1028
01:23:45,436 --> 01:23:46,728
[Samuel] Nolan!

1029
01:23:53,861 --> 01:23:54,861
Sam!

1030
01:23:59,951 --> 01:24:00,951
Sam!

1031
01:24:02,161 --> 01:24:03,829
Where are you?

1032
01:24:13,214 --> 01:24:14,965
- [rustles]
- [gasps]

1033
01:24:15,049 --> 01:24:16,717
- [clinks]
- No!

1034
01:24:18,177 --> 01:24:20,637
[ominous music plays]

1035
01:24:22,557 --> 01:24:24,100
[breathing heavily]

1036
01:24:26,852 --> 01:24:30,063
[panting]

1037
01:24:42,368 --> 01:24:45,204
[breathing heavily]

1038
01:24:49,458 --> 01:24:52,294
[door creaks, thuds]

1039
01:24:56,215 --> 01:24:57,215
Sam?

1040
01:25:07,018 --> 01:25:08,853
- [thudding upstairs]
- [gasps]

1041
01:25:18,529 --> 01:25:22,157
[floorboard creaking]

1042
01:25:34,920 --> 01:25:36,129
[whispering] It's not real.

1043
01:25:38,591 --> 01:25:39,800
It's not real.

1044
01:25:56,192 --> 01:25:58,194
[door creaks]

1045
01:26:06,577 --> 01:26:07,577
Sam.

1046
01:26:18,631 --> 01:26:20,132
Why did you cut my rope?

1047
01:26:36,273 --> 01:26:39,276
[ominous music playing]

1048
01:26:47,034 --> 01:26:48,034
Sam.

1049
01:26:50,329 --> 01:26:51,329
Sam.

1050
01:27:07,972 --> 01:27:10,307
O blessed house of ancient wood.

1051
01:27:11,600 --> 01:27:14,185
Shelter to the pure and good.

1052
01:27:14,270 --> 01:27:15,980
[yowling]

1053
01:27:16,063 --> 01:27:18,857
We'll keep you bright and never roam.

1054
01:27:18,941 --> 01:27:21,151
Heaven is here within our home!

1055
01:27:21,235 --> 01:27:22,945
[clinks]

1056
01:27:23,028 --> 01:27:26,031
- [grunts]
- [pants]

1057
01:27:28,784 --> 01:27:29,784
[yells]

1058
01:27:32,955 --> 01:27:34,206
Stop it, Sam!

1059
01:27:37,793 --> 01:27:39,044
Sam!

1060
01:27:39,128 --> 01:27:40,045
Sam!

1061
01:27:40,129 --> 01:27:41,672
[doorknob clacking]

1062
01:27:41,756 --> 01:27:42,756
Sam!

1063
01:27:43,466 --> 01:27:46,093
Sam! Sam!

1064
01:27:47,970 --> 01:27:48,970
Sam!

1065
01:27:49,013 --> 01:27:50,514
[whirring]

1066
01:27:56,395 --> 01:27:57,479
[effort grunts]

1067
01:27:58,481 --> 01:28:01,317
[panting]

1068
01:28:01,901 --> 01:28:02,901
Sam!

1069
01:28:04,028 --> 01:28:06,028
["The Big Rock Candy Mountain"
by Van Hunt playing]

1070
01:28:35,810 --> 01:28:37,895
[gasps, coughs]

1071
01:28:41,565 --> 01:28:43,567
[coughs, grunts]

1072
01:28:44,610 --> 01:28:47,237
Sam! You don't wanna do this!

1073
01:28:49,031 --> 01:28:52,659
[ominous music playing]

1074
01:28:53,661 --> 01:28:54,661
[grunts]

1075
01:29:01,252 --> 01:29:02,878
[gasping, coughing]

1076
01:29:02,962 --> 01:29:05,381
["The Big Rock Candy Mountain" continues]

1077
01:29:09,301 --> 01:29:11,136
[coughing]

1078
01:29:19,103 --> 01:29:20,103
[grunts]

1079
01:29:30,739 --> 01:29:32,699
[yelps, grunts]

1080
01:29:45,045 --> 01:29:47,213
The house won't protect you anymore.

1081
01:29:52,386 --> 01:29:54,096
[coughing]

1082
01:29:58,851 --> 01:29:59,851
[Momma] Nolan?

1083
01:30:05,608 --> 01:30:06,817
Come here, baby.

1084
01:30:09,403 --> 01:30:10,862
Come here.

1085
01:30:10,946 --> 01:30:13,114
I'm not mad at you, Nolan.

1086
01:30:13,198 --> 01:30:16,618
I was just like you when I was your age.

1087
01:30:18,954 --> 01:30:21,456
I wanna hold you again, baby.

1088
01:30:21,540 --> 01:30:22,541
Come on.

1089
01:30:31,634 --> 01:30:32,885
My sweet boy...

1090
01:30:34,511 --> 01:30:36,137
I missed you so much.

1091
01:30:37,932 --> 01:30:38,974
You're not her.

1092
01:30:40,517 --> 01:30:42,268
I-I saw what you did to Sam.

1093
01:30:42,353 --> 01:30:44,271
You saw What he really was.

1094
01:30:44,355 --> 01:30:45,898
I just helped him see it.

1095
01:30:51,111 --> 01:30:54,114
[dark music playing]

1096
01:31:08,545 --> 01:31:11,631
- [shutter clicks]
- [whirs]

1097
01:31:14,969 --> 01:31:16,679
Look at what you did.

1098
01:31:18,639 --> 01:31:20,891
You destroyed your whole family.

1099
01:31:21,600 --> 01:31:23,810
And I didn't even have to touch you.

1100
01:31:26,480 --> 01:31:27,772
I didn't mean to.

1101
01:31:27,856 --> 01:31:28,898
It's okay.

1102
01:31:28,983 --> 01:31:31,402
You don't have to be scared anymore.

1103
01:31:35,155 --> 01:31:37,073
You're not my Momma!

1104
01:31:37,157 --> 01:31:40,785
I'm more her than she ever was.

1105
01:31:42,162 --> 01:31:45,748
I'm the darkness that was inside her.

1106
01:31:47,543 --> 01:31:49,962
I'm the darkness that's inside you now.

1107
01:31:50,045 --> 01:31:53,423
I'm the darkness that's in your blood.

1108
01:31:53,507 --> 01:31:54,799
All you got to do...

1109
01:31:56,552 --> 01:31:57,970
is let go.

1110
01:32:01,306 --> 01:32:02,640
I can't!

1111
01:32:06,478 --> 01:32:10,978
["The Big Rock Candy Mountain" playing]

1112
01:32:16,155 --> 01:32:17,656
- [sobbing]
- [flames intensify]

1113
01:32:26,248 --> 01:32:30,748
[distorted playing]

1114
01:32:45,642 --> 01:32:48,519
There's nothing for you in that cellar.

1115
01:32:51,690 --> 01:32:54,609
[grunting]

1116
01:32:54,693 --> 01:32:57,654
- [yelling]
- [grunting]

1117
01:32:59,948 --> 01:33:01,115
[door opens]

1118
01:33:06,121 --> 01:33:07,288
Did you imagine it?

1119
01:33:07,372 --> 01:33:08,372
Yes.

1120
01:33:09,958 --> 01:33:11,084
Tell us about it.

1121
01:33:12,127 --> 01:33:14,462
[Nolan] <i>I thought about
our birth in the house</i>

1122
01:33:14,546 --> 01:33:16,381
<i>and how safe it keeps us every day.</i>

1123
01:33:17,382 --> 01:33:19,675
And I felt the darkness float away.

1124
01:33:19,760 --> 01:33:23,138
- [screaming]
- [grunting]

1125
01:33:23,222 --> 01:33:25,807
When we remember why we're holding on

1126
01:33:25,891 --> 01:33:27,642
<i>and who we holding on for...</i>

1127
01:33:29,269 --> 01:33:30,603
- [grunting]
- [screaming]

1128
01:33:32,314 --> 01:33:33,606
- [grunting]
- [thudding]

1129
01:33:33,690 --> 01:33:35,608
We get strong again.

1130
01:33:35,692 --> 01:33:36,734
[screams]

1131
01:33:36,819 --> 01:33:38,862
The Evil can't touch me here.

1132
01:33:38,946 --> 01:33:41,114
Dawn to night and year to year.

1133
01:33:41,198 --> 01:33:44,492
- [screaming]
- [grunting]

1134
01:33:45,452 --> 01:33:48,455
O blessed house of ancient wood.

1135
01:33:49,164 --> 01:33:51,332
<i>Shelter to the pure and good.</i>

1136
01:33:51,416 --> 01:33:52,417
Never let go.

1137
01:33:52,501 --> 01:33:53,585
Never let go.

1138
01:33:53,669 --> 01:33:56,505
- [Momma grunting]
- We'll keep you bright and never roam.

1139
01:33:56,588 --> 01:33:58,590
Heaven is here within our home.

1140
01:34:10,477 --> 01:34:12,312
I love you, Momma!

1141
01:34:18,527 --> 01:34:21,530
[somber music playing]

1142
01:35:01,361 --> 01:35:02,570
[breathes heavily]

1143
01:35:27,846 --> 01:35:30,849
[uneasy music playing]

1144
01:35:41,568 --> 01:35:43,987
[whirring]

1145
01:35:52,412 --> 01:35:53,412
[barks]

1146
01:35:54,706 --> 01:35:56,165
[panting]

1147
01:36:10,889 --> 01:36:13,600
My brother. I need to find my brother.

1148
01:36:13,684 --> 01:36:15,036
- [medic] You're safe now.
- My brother.

1149
01:36:15,060 --> 01:36:16,996
- But we can't leave him.
- You're safe just now. Just breathe.

1150
01:36:17,020 --> 01:36:19,580
- No! Where is he? Where is he?
- Just breathe now. Just breathe.

1151
01:36:19,606 --> 01:36:21,441
- [panting]
- It's okay. He's right here.

1152
01:36:26,154 --> 01:36:27,154
Sam.

1153
01:36:27,197 --> 01:36:28,198
Sam.

1154
01:36:30,158 --> 01:36:33,411
I'm here. Hey, Sam. I'm here, Sam.

1155
01:36:34,037 --> 01:36:35,079
I'm here.

1156
01:36:37,874 --> 01:36:38,916
We're free.

1157
01:37:07,237 --> 01:37:08,321
We're free.

1158
01:37:17,914 --> 01:37:19,415
She loves me more.

1159
01:37:23,712 --> 01:37:27,716
["Goodnight, Mother" by Dick Todd
with Orchestra playing]

1160
01:39:50,108 --> 01:39:51,400
[song ends]

1161
01:39:56,531 --> 01:39:59,534
[ominous music playing]

1162
01:41:18,113 --> 01:41:19,322
[music ends]

